{"type":"message","id":"4436dfb5","parentId":"621c683d","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:49:42.399Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"用户询问是否可以开始测试 xiaodouya MCP。从搜索结果来看，我找到了几个相关的 MCP 文件：\n\n1. `/home/yirongbest/.openclaw/workspace/xiaodouya/xiaodouya_mcp_server.py` - 小豆芽 MCP 服务器\n2. `/home/yirongbest/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-mcp-plugin` - MCP 插件\n3. 虚拟环境中安装了 mcp 包\n\n让我检查一下 xiaodouya MCP 服务器的具体内容，以及它是否已经配置好了。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"让我检查一下 xiaodouya MCP 服务器的配置和状态。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read:8","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/yirongbest/.openclaw/workspace/xiaodouya/xiaodouya_mcp_server.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read:9","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/yirongbest/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-mcp-plugin/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"volcengine-plan","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":22631,"output":317,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22948,"cost":{"input":0.0000022631,"output":6.34e-8,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0000023265}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772250573100}}
{"type":"message","id":"0d3b2b86","parentId":"4436dfb5","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:49:42.408Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read:8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Optional\n\nfrom controller import XiaodouyaController, load_selectors, validate_selectors_schema\nfrom publish_xiaohongshu import (\n    DEFAULT_EVIDENCE_ROOT,\n    DEFAULT_SELECTORS_PATH,\n    STEP_ORDER,\n    run_workflow,\n)\n\ntry:\n    from mcp.server.fastmcp import FastMCP\nexcept ImportError as exc:  # pragma: no cover\n    raise SystemExit(f\"Missing dependency: {exc}. Install with `pip install mcp`.\")\n\n\nmcp = FastMCP(\"xiaodouya-linux-win-control\")\n\n\ndef _selectors_path(selectors_path: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n    return Path(selectors_path) if selectors_path else DEFAULT_SELECTORS_PATH\n\n\ndef _evidence_root(evidence_dir: Optional[str]) -> Path:\n    return Path(evidence_dir) if evidence_dir else DEFAULT_EVIDENCE_ROOT\n\n\ndef _status_from_jsonl(path: Path) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    if not path.exists():\n        return {\"ok\": False, \"error\": f\"jsonl report not found: {path}\"}\n\n    lines = path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\").splitlines()\n    if not lines:\n        return {\"ok\": False, \"error\": \"jsonl report is empty\"}\n\n    last = json.loads(lines[-1])\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"events\": len(lines),\n        \"last_event\": last,\n        \"prepublish_ready\": bool(last.get(\"step\") in {\"screenshot_prepublish\", \"publish_click\"} and last.get(\"ok\")),\n    }\n\n\ndef _controller_for_runtime(selectors_path: Optional[str], evidence_dir: Optional[str]) -> XiaodouyaController:\n    return XiaodouyaController(\n        selectors_path=_selectors_path(selectors_path),\n        evidence_dir=_evidence_root(evidence_dir),\n    )\n\n\n@mcp.tool()\ndef xdy_run_workflow(\n    content_file: str,\n    mode: str = \"prepublish\",\n    resume_from: Optional[str] = None,\n    evidence_dir: Optional[str] = None,\n    run_id: Optional[str] = None,\n    selectors_path: Optional[str] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Run full workflow: attach/start -> fill content -> prepublish/publish.\"\"\"\n    return run_workflow(\n        content_file=content_file,\n        mode=mode,\n        resume_from=resume_from,\n        evidence_dir=evidence_dir,\n        run_id=run_id,\n        selectors_path=selectors_path,\n    )\n\n\n@mcp.tool()\ndef xdy_step(\n    step: str,\n    action: str = \"wait_for\",\n    text: str = \"\",\n    selectors_path: Optional[str] = None,\n    evidence_dir: Optional[str] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Execute one step action: wait_for/click/type_text/screenshot/activate/attach_or_start.\"\"\"\n    controller = _controller_for_runtime(selectors_path, evidence_dir)\n\n    if action == \"attach_or_start\":\n        return controller.attach_or_start()\n    if action == \"activate\":\n        return controller.activate()\n    if action == \"wait_for\":\n        return controller.wait_for(step)\n    if action == \"click\":\n        return controller.click(step)\n    if action == \"type_text\":\n        return controller.type_text(step, text)\n    if action == \"screenshot\":\n        return controller.screenshot(step)\n\n    return {\"ok\": False, \"error\": f\"unsupported action: {action}\"}\n\n\n@mcp.tool()\ndef xdy_resume(\n    run_id: str,\n    content_file: str,\n    mode: str = \"prepublish\",\n    resume_from: Optional[str] = None,\n    evidence_dir: Optional[str] = None,\n    selectors_path: Optional[str] = None,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Resume workflow from explicit step or auto-detected failed step from jsonl.\"\"\"\n    root = _evidence_root(evidence_dir)\n    run_dir = root / run_id\n    jsonl_path = run_dir / f\"run_report_{run_id}.jsonl\"\n\n    start_step = resume_from\n    if start_step is None and jsonl_path.exists():\n        events = [json.loads(line) for line in jsonl_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\").splitlines() if line.strip()]\n        failed = [e for e in events if not e.get(\"ok\")]\n        if failed:\n            start_step = failed[-1][\"step\"]\n\n    if start_step is None:\n        start_step = STEP_ORDER[0]\n\n    return run_workflow(\n        content_file=content_file,\n        mode=mode,\n        resume_from=start_step,\n        evidence_dir=str(root),\n        run_id=run_id,\n        selectors_path=selectors_path,\n    )\n\n\n@mcp.tool()\ndef xdy_get_status(run_id: str, evidence_dir: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Get run status by reading run_report_<id>.jsonl/md.\"\"\"\n    root = _evidence_root(evidence_dir)\n    run_dir = root / run_id\n    jsonl_path = run_dir / f\"run_report_{run_id}.jsonl\"\n    md_path = run_dir / f\"run_report_{run_id}.md\"\n\n    status = _status_from_jsonl(jsonl_path)\n    status.update(\n        {\n            \"run_id\": run_id,\n            \"report_jsonl\": str(jsonl_path),\n            \"report_md\": str(md_path),\n            \"report_md_exists\": md_path.exists(),\n        }\n    )\n    return status\n\n\n@mcp.tool()\ndef xdy_list_selectors(selectors_path: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"List current selectors map.\"\"\"\n    path = _selectors_path(selectors_path)\n    selectors = load_selectors(path)\n    return {\"ok\": True, \"selectors_path\": str(path), \"selectors\": selectors}\n\n\n@mcp.tool()\ndef xdy_validate_selectors(selectors_path: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Validate selector schema and minimum strategy count.\"\"\"\n    path = _selectors_path(selectors_path)\n    selectors = load_selectors(path)\n    errors = validate_selectors_schema(selectors)\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"selectors_path\": str(path),\n        \"errors\": errors,\n    }\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    mcp.run()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772250582407}}
{"type":"message","id":"a4334814","parentId":"0d3b2b86","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:49:42.411Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read:9","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: mcp-integration\ndescription: Use Model Context Protocol servers to access external tools and data sources. Enable AI agents to discover and execute tools from configured MCP servers (legal databases, APIs, database connectors, weather services, etc.).\nlicense: MIT\n---\n\n# MCP Integration Usage Guide\n\n## Overview\n\nUse the MCP integration plugin to discover and execute tools provided by external MCP servers. This skill enables you to access legal databases, query APIs, search databases, and integrate with any service that provides an MCP interface.\n\nThe plugin provides a unified `mcp` tool with two actions:\n- `list` - Discover available tools from all connected servers\n- `call` - Execute a specific tool with parameters\n\n---\n\n# Process\n\n## 🔍 Phase 1: Tool Discovery\n\n### 1.1 Check Available Tools\n\n**Always start by listing available tools** to see what MCP servers are connected and what capabilities they provide.\n\n**Action:**\n```\n{\n  tool: \"mcp\",\n  args: {\n    action: \"list\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Response structure:**\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"id\": \"server:toolname\",\n    \"server\": \"server-name\",\n    \"name\": \"tool-name\", \n    \"description\": \"What this tool does\",\n    \"inputSchema\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"properties\": {...},\n      \"required\": [...]\n    }\n  }\n]\n```\n\n### 1.2 Understand Tool Schemas\n\nFor each tool, examine:\n- **id**: Format is `\"server:toolname\"` - split on `:` to get server and tool names\n- **description**: Understand what the tool does\n- **inputSchema**: JSON Schema defining parameters\n  - `properties`: Available parameters with types and descriptions\n  - `required`: Array of mandatory parameter names\n\n### 1.3 Match Tools to User Requests\n\nCommon tool naming patterns:\n- `search_*` - Find or search operations (e.g., `search_statute`, `search_users`)\n- `get_*` - Retrieve specific data (e.g., `get_statute_full_text`, `get_weather`)\n- `query` - Execute queries (e.g., `database:query`)\n- `analyze_*` - Analysis operations (e.g., `analyze_law`)\n- `resolve_*` - Resolve references (e.g., `resolve_citation`)\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Phase 2: Tool Execution\n\n### 2.1 Validate Parameters\n\nBefore calling a tool:\n1. Identify all required parameters from `inputSchema.required`\n2. Verify parameter types match schema (string, number, boolean, array, object)\n3. Check for constraints (minimum, maximum, enum values, patterns)\n4. Ensure you have necessary information from the user\n\n### 2.2 Construct Tool Call\n\n**Action:**\n```\n{\n  tool: \"mcp\",\n  args: {\n    action: \"call\",\n    server: \"<server-name>\",\n    tool: \"<tool-name>\",\n    args: {\n      // Tool-specific parameters from inputSchema\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Example - Korean legal search:**\n```\n{\n  tool: \"mcp\",\n  args: {\n    action: \"call\",\n    server: \"kr-legal\",\n    tool: \"search_statute\",\n    args: {\n      query: \"연장근로 수당\",\n      limit: 5\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 2.3 Parse Response\n\nTool responses follow this structure:\n```json\n{\n  \"content\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"text\",\n      \"text\": \"JSON string or text result\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"isError\": false\n}\n```\n\nFor JSON responses:\n```javascript\nconst data = JSON.parse(response.content[0].text);\n// Access data.result, data.results, or direct properties\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 Phase 3: Multi-Step Workflows\n\n### 3.1 Chain Tool Calls\n\nFor complex requests, execute multiple tools in sequence:\n\n**Example - Legal research workflow:**\n1. **Search** - `search_statute` to find relevant laws\n2. **Retrieve** - `get_statute_full_text` for complete text\n3. **Analyze** - `analyze_law` for interpretation\n4. **Precedents** - `search_case_law` for related cases\n\nEach step uses output from the previous step to inform the next call.\n\n### 3.2 Maintain Context\n\nBetween tool calls:\n- Extract relevant information from each response\n- Use extracted data as parameters for subsequent calls\n- Build up understanding progressively\n- Present synthesized results to user\n\n---\n\n## ⚠ Phase 4: Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Common Errors\n\n**\"Tool not found: server:toolname\"**\n- Cause: Server not connected or tool doesn't exist\n- Solution: Run `action: \"list\"` to verify available tools\n- Check spelling of server and tool names\n\n**\"Invalid arguments for tool\"**\n- Cause: Missing required parameter or wrong type\n- Solution: Review `inputSchema` from list response\n- Ensure all required parameters provided with correct types\n\n**\"Server connection failed\"**\n- Cause: MCP server not running or unreachable\n- Solution: Inform user service is temporarily unavailable\n- Suggest alternatives if possible\n\n### 4.2 Error Response Format\n\nErrors return:\n```json\n{\n  \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Error: message\"}],\n  \"isError\": true\n}\n```\n\n**Handle gracefully:**\n- Explain what went wrong clearly\n- Don't expose technical implementation details\n- Suggest next steps or alternatives\n- Don't retry excessively\n\n---\n\n# Complete Example\n\n## User Request: \"Find Korean laws about overtime pay\"\n\n### Step 1: Discover tools\n```\n{tool: \"mcp\", args: {action: \"list\"}}\n```\n\nResponse shows `kr-legal:search_statute` with:\n- Required: `query` (string)\n- Optional: `limit` (number), `category` (string)\n\n### Step 2: Execute search\n```\n{\n  tool: \"mcp\",\n  args: {\n    action: \"call\",\n    server: \"kr-legal\",\n    tool: \"search_statute\",\n    args: {\n      query: \"연장근로 수당\",\n      category: \"노동법\",\n      limit: 5\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Step 3: Parse and present\n```javascript\nconst data = JSON.parse(response.content[0].text);\n// Present data.results to user\n```\n\n**User-facing response:**\n```\nFound 5 Korean statutes about overtime pay:\n\n1. 근로기준법 제56조 (연장·야간 및 휴일 근로)\n   - Overtime work requires 50% premium\n   \n2. 근로기준법 제50조 (근로시간)\n   - Standard working hours: 40 hours per week\n\nWould you like me to retrieve the full text of any statute?\n```\n\n---\n\n# Quick Reference\n\n## List Tools\n```\n{tool: \"mcp\", args: {action: \"list\"}}\n```\n\n## Call Tool\n```\n{\n  tool: \"mcp\",\n  args: {\n    action: \"call\",\n    server: \"server-name\",\n    tool: \"tool-name\",\n    args: {param1: \"value1\"}\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Essential Patterns\n\n**Tool ID parsing:** `\"server:toolname\"` → split on `:` for server and tool names\n\n**Parameter validation:** Check `inputSchema.required` and `inputSchema.properties[param].type`\n\n**Response parsing:** `JSON.parse(response.content[0].text)` for JSON responses\n\n**Error detection:** Check `response.isError === true`\n\n---\n\n# Reference Documentation\n\n## Core Documentation\n\n- **Plugin README**: [README.md](README.md) - Installation and configuration\n- **Real Example**: [REAL_EXAMPLE_KR_LEGAL.md](docs/REAL_EXAMPLE_KR_LEGAL.md) - Working kr-legal setup\n- **API Reference**: [API.md](docs/API.md) - Technical API details\n- **Configuration**: [CONFIGURATION.md](docs/CONFIGURATION.md) - Server configuration guide\n- **Troubleshooting**: [TROUBLESHOOTING.md](docs/TROUBLESHOOTING.md) - Common issues and solutions\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n- **Examples Collection**: [EXAMPLES.md](docs/EXAMPLES.md) - 13 real-world examples including:\n  - Legal research workflows\n  - Database queries\n  - Weather service integration\n  - Multi-step complex workflows\n  - Error handling patterns\n\n---\n\n**Remember:** Always start with `action: \"list\"` when uncertain about available tools.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772250582410}}
