{"type":"message","id":"698f411a","parentId":"181bc00a","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:55:46.615Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read:48","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"mcp-integration\",\n  \"name\": \"MCP Integration\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Model Context Protocol (MCP) integration - connect to MCP servers and use their tools\",\n  \"author\": \"Lob\",\n  \"license\": \"MIT\",\n  \"openclaw\": {\n    \"minVersion\": \"2026.1.0\"\n  },\n  \"configSchema\": {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"additionalProperties\": false,\n    \"properties\": {\n      \"enabled\": {\n        \"type\": \"boolean\",\n        \"default\": true\n      },\n      \"servers\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\",\n        \"description\": \"MCP servers to connect to\",\n        \"additionalProperties\": {\n          \"type\": \"object\",\n          \"properties\": {\n            \"enabled\": {\n              \"type\": \"boolean\",\n              \"default\": true\n            },\n            \"transport\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\",\n              \"enum\": [\"http\", \"stdio\"],\n              \"description\": \"Transport type\"\n            },\n            \"url\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\",\n              \"description\": \"HTTP URL (for http transport)\"\n            },\n            \"command\": {\n              \"type\": \"string\",\n              \"description\": \"Command to spawn (for stdio transport)\"\n            },\n            \"args\": {\n              \"type\": \"array\",\n              \"items\": {\n                \"type\": \"string\"\n              },\n              \"description\": \"Command arguments (for stdio transport)\"\n            },\n            \"env\": {\n              \"type\": \"object\",\n              \"additionalProperties\": {\n                \"type\": \"string\"\n              },\n              \"description\": \"Environment variables (for stdio transport)\"\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772250946614}}
{"type":"message","id":"57fee446","parentId":"698f411a","timestamp":"2026-02-28T03:56:24.236Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"根据我的检查，目前 xiaodouya MCP 服务器的情况如下：\n\n## 当前状态\n\n**✅ MCP 服务器已就绪**\n- 服务器名称: `xiaodouya-linux-win-control`\n- 服务器类型: FastMCP\n- 已注册 8 个工具\n\n**📦 可用工具列表:**\n1. `xdy_run_workflow` - 运行完整工作流\n2. `xdy_step` - 执行单个步骤\n3. `xdy_resume` - 恢复工作流\n4. `xdy_get_status` - 获取运行状态\n5. `xdy_list_selectors` - 列出选择器\n6. `xdy_validate_selectors` - 验证选择器\n\n**⚠️ 但存在配置问题:**\n1. OpenClaw MCP 插件 (`openclaw-mcp-plugin`) 尚未安装到 `~/.openclaw/extensions/`\n2. `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` 中没有配置 MCP 服务器\n\n## 需要完成的步骤\n\n**方案A：通过 OpenClaw MCP 插件（推荐）**\n1. 将 `skills/openclaw-mcp-plugin` 安装到 `~/.openclaw/extensions/`\n2. 配置 `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` 添加 xiaodouya MCP 服务器\n3. 重启 OpenClaw gateway\n\n**方案B：直接通过子进程调用**\n- 直接运行 `xiaodouya/xiaodouya_mcp_server.py` 并通过 subprocess 调用工具\n\n用户问\"可以开始测试xiaodouya mcp了吗\"，我需要告诉他们当前状态以及需要什么才能开始测试。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"根据我的检查，**xiaodouya MCP 服务器已经准备好，但还需要一些配置才能通过 OpenClaw 进行测试**。\n\n## 📊 当前状态\n\n### ✅ 已完成\n- **MCP 服务器代码**: `xiaodouya/xiaodouya_mcp_server.py` 已就绪\n- **8 个可用工具**:\n  - `xdy_run_workflow` - 运行完整工作流\n  - `xdy_step` - 执行单个步骤\n  - `xdy_resume` - 恢复工作流\n  - `xdy_get_status` - 获取运行状态\n  - `xdy_list_selectors` - 列出选择器\n  - `xdy_validate_selectors` - 验证选择器配置\n\n### ⚠️ 还缺少\n1. **OpenClaw MCP 插件未安装** - `skills/openclaw-mcp-plugin` 需要复制到 `~/.openclaw/extensions/`\n2. **配置文件未更新** - 需要在 `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` 中添加 xiaodouya MCP 服务器配置\n\n## 🚀 开始测试\n\n需要我帮你完成以下步骤吗？\n\n**选项 A：完整配置（推荐）**\n1. 安装 MCP 插件到 OpenClaw\n2. 配置 xiaodouya MCP 服务器\n3. 重启 OpenClaw gateway\n4. 测试工具调用\n\n**选项 B：直接测试（快速）**\n直接运行 `xiaodouya_mcp_server.py` 并通过 Python 脚本调用工具，不经过 OpenClaw MCP 插件\n\n你想选择哪种方式开始测试？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"volcengine-plan","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":41356,"output":1068,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42424,"cost":{"input":0.0